wsdl:definitions.wsdl:documentation: This web service provides methods for retrieving and updating information in the Resource Enterprise system. For detailed information about the methods contained in this web service, please contact Resource Systems customer support at 1-800-338-3681.

wsdl:operation.name: TestMethod
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method is here as a basic test of connectivity to the the web service.

wsdl:operation.name: ImportDataFromDevice
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: INTERNAL USE ONLY. This method is used to import data from handheld device related information to client.

wsdl:operation.name: ValidateDeviceUser
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: INTERNAL USE ONLY. This method is used to validate the user of the portable device. The password is encrypted.

wsdl:operation.name: ExportDataToDevice
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: INTERNAL USE ONLY. This method is used to send data to handheld device on client workstation.

wsdl:operation.name: PurgeResident
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Removes resident from system. This includes any existing data relating to the resident including observations, scheduling information, etc

wsdl:operation.name: PurgeResidentCensusAll
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Removes all census information pertaining to the resident from system.

wsdl:operation.name: PurgeResidentCensusFromDate
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Removes census information pertaining to the resident from system greater than or equal to the date/time passed in.

wsdl:operation.name: RetrieveData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method is used to retrieve data from the Enterprise database using existing interface reports. There are two interface reports available in the default installation, compressed ADL and observation detail. Other interface reports can be setup by request. The XML stream being passed in will be validated against the InputParameters.xsd schema file. Data will be returned in the format specified for the requested interface report. If errors are encountered a dataset containing error information will be returned.

wsdl:operation.name: RetrieveDataURL
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method is used to retrieve the url of the PDF file generated by the reporting system for the requested interface report. There are two interface reports available in the default installation, compressed ADL and observation detail. Other interface reports can be setup by request. The XML stream being passed in will be validated against the InputParameters.xsd schema file. If errors are encountered a url to an error page will be returned.

wsdl:operation.name: RetrieveDataByFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method is used to retrieve data from the Enterprise database using existing interface reports. The file name is passed to the method. This is the name of the file with no path information included. The file must be transferred to a LoadFiles folder on the Enterprise web site before it can be loaded. The file will be deleted from the loadfiles folder after processing regardless of the outcome. The file will be validated against the InputParameters.xsd schema file. There are two interface reports available in the default installation, compressed ADL and observation detail. Other interface reports can be setup by request. Data will be returned in the format specified for the requested interface report. If errors are encountered a dataset containing the error information will be returned.

wsdl:operation.name: ValidateData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method is used to validate XML streams that are used as input to the methods. The first parameter is the actual XML stream. The second parameter is FileCategory. Available file categories are Resident, Census, Staff, Item, Protocol and InputParameters. A dataset containing validation errors will be returned.

wsdl:operation.name: ValidateDataByFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method is used to validate files that are used as input to the methods. The first parameter is FileName. This is the name of the file with no path information included. The file must be transferred to a LoadFiles folder on the Enterprise web site before it can be validated. The file will be deleted from the loadfiles folder after processing regardless of the outcome. The second parameter is FileType. Available file types are XML and CSV. The third parameter is FileCategory. Available file categories are Resident, Census, Staff, Item, and InputParameters. InputParameters validation does not support the CSV type. A dataset containing validation errors will be returned.

wsdl:operation.name: ModifyData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method is used to add, update or delete data in the Enterprise database using an XML stream. The first parameter is the actual XML stream. The second parameter is FileCategory. Available file categories are Resident, Census, Staff, Item, Protocol. A dataset containing any errors in the input data will be returned. If no errors are encountered than an empty dataset will be returned.

wsdl:operation.name: ModifyDataByFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: This method is used to add, update or delete data in the Enterprise database using a file. The first parameter is FileName. This is the name of the file with no path information included. The file must be transferred to a LoadFiles folder on the Enterprise web site before it can be loaded. The file will be deleted from the loadfiles folder after processing regardless of the outcome. The second parameter is FileType. Available file types are XML and CSV. The third parameter is FileCategory. Available file categories are Resident, Census, Staff, and Item. A dataset containing any errors in the input data will be returned. If no errors are encountered than an empty dataset will be returned.
